parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission shift cable can cause the manual gear shifter to disengage from the transmission, leaving the driver unable to shift into gear, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded in traffic.
symptoms: The manual gear shifter feels disconnected
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear
the vehicle is stuck in neutral
the driver is unable to shift into lower gears
the transmission cable is visible on the floor.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seatbelt retraction mechanism can cause the seatbelts to not retract properly, which can lead to reduced safety in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seatbelts only retract halfway
the seatbelts do not retract at all
the seatbelts are stuck in a partially retracted position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cylinder head can cause the engine to overheat, leading to a loss of power, stalling, or even engine failure, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Engine overheating
fluid leaking from underneath the vehicle
cracked cylinder head
engine stalling or failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning unit can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: Air conditioning unit stops cooling
fuse issues
faulty diode.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become difficult to shift, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Whining noise in 2nd and 3rd gear
low transmission fluid level
internal metal fracture in transaxle inner case
blown seal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the emergency brake handle can render the emergency brake inoperable, leading to a loss of vehicle control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The emergency brake button pops off
the emergency brake is inoperable
the vehicle is unable to be secured on an incline.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive brake pedal travel can increase stopping distances, leading to a higher risk of accidents and reducing vehicle safety.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes all the way to the floor
the stopping distance has increased
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.
